    "title": "Template Sharing Tracking Issue",
    "body": "Plan:\n\n * Protocol specification [BIN25-2](https://github.com/bitcoin-inquisition/binana/blob/master/2025/BIN-2025-0002.md) and [BIP153 PR#1937](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/pull/1937)\n * Implementation:\n   * (See comments below)\n * Live tests\n   * (See comments below)\n   * [ ] inquisition.bitcoin-signet.net\n   * [x] mainnet: cornflower.erisian.com.au provides templates currently\n   * [ ] warnet simulation?\n * Discussion:\n   * https://delvingbitcoin.org/t/sharing-block-templates/1906\n * Potential benefits: (tick with data confirming benefit)\n   * [ ] Quick population of mempool on initial start\n   * [ ] Quicker relay of top-of-mempool transactions \n   * [ ] Improved compact block propagation with diverse mempool policies\n   * [ ] Transaction rebroadcast without participation of sender/receiver\n * Future ideas:\n   * [x] Include 2MvB of transactions, not just the next block\n   * [x] Send templates shortly after construction\n   * [x] Coordinate template construction with INV announcements better\n   * [x] Send diffs since prior templates to reduce bandwidth\n   * [ ] Use set reconciliation to improve compact block reconstruction (see delving discussion)\n   * [ ] Use reduced siphash to make compact block calculations faster?\n",
